rComments: Myriam is the nicest prof, she always makes class fun and lighthearted. Workload is very reasonable, 4 homeworks (only best 3 count) and a final. The homework is very straightforward. She is always understanding and accomodates for the stress of online school. No textbook, just optional readings. :)

Myriam is the sweetest teacher out there She cares so much about her students and the content. Class is always fun and she really makes an effort to be reasonable and understanding in her grading. She is always available when you need extra help and makes semantics very fun. Very manageable workload, 3 homework exercises, midterm, and a final. :)

She is a sweetheart. Her assessments are not hard at all. The course was simple not too much workload. If you have any issue she will take care of it. There was 1 midterm, 1 exam, and 3 hwrks. She is also fun to be watching in an online lecture!

10/10 would recommend a class with her! She is so kind and great at explaining the material. No textbook or lecture slides, but her handouts for each class were concise and had everything we needed. Lectures were very interesting & fun. Exam/Assignments were fair and reflected exactly what we had learned. LOVED this prof!!!

I cannot say enough good things about Professor Dali. Really caring and kind; she explains complicated topics gradually so you can follow along. The class isn't easy, but Myriam makes it enjoyable and pleasant, and is a fair grader. Very accessable outside the class for office hours. Would definitely reccommend.

Just overall a nice prof. Was available on zoom during our exam to answer questions. Spent the first half of the semester reviewing first year linguistics concepts as they applied to the class. Each lecture had a clear learning goal and she ensured that the topic was covered sufficiently within the time. Always open to answer questions in class.

Myriam cared about all of the students and knew a lot of us by name. She is kind and always makes sure that we did our work and understood what we were doing. The TAs were kind of useless. Most of us finished the exam within the first 45 minutes. Funny, always made jokes and kept us awake and interested early in the morning
she was super nice and truly caring for her students, I wish she was now my syntax teacher.
